I think carrots and carrot tops are every bit as pretty as flowers! And with the price of flowers these days, I’m opting for props I can at least eat (‘cause veggies aren’t cheap either ;)

Having said that, I’m heading to Trader Joe’s today and perhaps I’ll find a reasonably priced bouquet 🤞🏻 

PS .. I don’t usually buy organic but I have to say these were the sweetest carrots ever!

Today I’m looking forward to getting outside and enjoying the warmer weather we’re about to have. Even though everything is brown and dry, there are clay pots to clean, flower pots to dig out from under the deck, and a bit of patio furniture to repair, because .. well .. 🐿️ 😩

Since we’ve been home, I’ve heard Canada Geese, loons, redwing blackbirds, coyotes, and observed a lot of bunnies running around .. things are moving along 🍃

Have a lovely weekend my friends!

A favourite window situation.. flowers on my little whitewashed tabletop ✨

Today on my blog I’m sharing how to style a linen serviette (with an added extra handy tip for you). For me, one of the most challenging props to style is a simple piece of fabric .. the humble serviette/napkin. I prefer to use linen as opposed to cotton as linen drapes and flows in a much more interesting way. See my post to learn more (link in profile).
